Plan Item #182490: [go_router_builder] Support custom Codec or Converter for TypedQueryParameter

### Use case

We've recently gotten back a pentest warning that numberic IDs in our url could allow others to guess other valid pages. Even though this is a very minor warning and we have a more secure permission based security model in place, it would still be a boon if the path or query params could be encrypted more easily.

For now we are encrypting the params before passing them into the Route and decrypting it before passing it into the Page.

Example: 
```dart
extension EncryptedString on String {
  static int encrypt(String i) => //...;
  int decrypt() => //...;
}

@TypedGoRoute<TopPage1Route>(path: '/top/:pathId')
class TopPage1Route extends GoRouteData with $TopPage1Route {
  const TopPage1Route({
    required this.pathId,
    @TypedQueryParameter(name: 'q') this.optionalQueryId,
    required this.$extra,
  });

  final int pathId;
  final String? optionalQueryId;
  final int $extra;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, GoRouterState state) =>
      TopPage1(pathId: pathId, optionalQueryId: optionalQueryId?.decrypt(), extra: $extra);
}
```





### Proposal

Using the `go_router_builder` I thought that the newly added `TypedQueryParameter` could possibly accept a Codec or mapper method which allows for this encryption use case.
Otherwise it might be handy to have an additional param next to the `GoRouter.extraCodec` to trigger on all path and query params.

